value.value: The degree of de- or hyperpolarization or number of action potentials in response to a specific stimulus recorded in a single cell.
Any measurable characteristic related to the electrophysiological recording of the activity of several cells.
The point at which a stimulus first elicits a recordable response recorded in several cells or a tissue slice.
The degree of de- or hyperpolarization or number of action potentials in response to a specific stimulus recorded in several cells or a tissue slice.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the capacity to change, adjust, or alter the electrophysiological recordings from the elongated processes of neurons over time or as a result of internal or external influences.
The point at which a stimulus first elicits a recordable response recorded in a single or several nerve fiber(s).
The degree of de- or hyperpolarization or number of action potentials in response to a specific stimulus recorded in a single or several nerve fiber(s).

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the capacity to change, adjust, or alter the electrophysiological recordings from ion channels over time or as a result of internal or external influences.
The point at which a stimulus first elicits a recordable response recorded from ion channels.
The degree of de- or hyperpolarization or number of action potentials in response to a specific stimulus recorded from ion channels.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to coordinated movements executed with a purpose that can be improved by learning and/or experience.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to movements that occur independent of planning (e.g. reflexive behavior).

The proportion or number of cells in the two-lobed endocrine gland found in all vertebrates, located in front of and on either side of the trachea in humans, that produces various hormones, such as triiodothyronine and calcitonin.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to thyroid function in oxidation and organification of iodide.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the controlled release of growth hormone.
Any measurable characteristic related to the function of or processes in the female reproductive gland containing the germ cells.
The proportion, quantity, or volume in whole blood, serum, or plasma of this potent androgenic metabolite of testosterone.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color, or pattern of the folds of skin which form the inner lips (labia minora) and outer lips (labia majora) on both sides of the vaginal opening.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the physical magnitude of the folds of skin which form the inner lips (labia minora) and outer lips (labia majora) on both sides of the vaginal opening.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color, or pattern of grooves or furrows in the folds of skin between the labia on both sides of the vaginal opening.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color, or pattern of the folds of skin which form the outer lips (labia majora) on both sides of the vaginal opening.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the physical magnitude of the folds of skin which form the outer lips (labia majora) on both sides of the vaginal opening.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the physical form or contours of the folds of skin which form the outer lips (labia majora) on both sides of the vaginal opening.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color, or pattern of the folds of skin which form the inner lips (labia minora) on both sides of the vaginal opening.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the physical magnitude of the folds of skin which form the inner lips (labia minora) on both sides of the vaginal opening.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the physical form or contours of the folds of skin which form the inner lips (labia minora) on both sides of the vaginal opening.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the physical magnitude of the external genitalia of the female.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the physical magnitude of the small, erectile body located at the anterior end of the vulva.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the morphology or physiology of the female reproductive canal located between the uterus and the vulva during its formation and differentiation.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the morphology or physiology during formation or differentiation of the thin membrane which may partially occlude the opening of the vagina; often absent in normal females.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color, or pattern of the loose fold of skin that covers the penis.
Any measurable characteristic related to the function of or processes in the insulin-producing cells of the islets of Langerhans in the pancreas.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the function of or processes in the glucagon-producing cells of the islets of Langerhans in the pancreas.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the controlled release of this hormone secreted by beta cells of the pancreas, which promotes glucose utilization, protein synthesis, and the formation and storage of neutral lipids.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the controlled release of this hormone secreted by the alpha cells of the islets of Langerhans; it normally plays a role in regulation of blood glucose concentration, ketone metabolism, and other biochemical and physiological processes.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color, or pattern of the opening or lumen of the uterus.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the morphology or physiology during formation and differentiation of the hollow muscular organ where the embryo/fetus develops.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color, or pattern of the tube through which the ova pass from the ovary to the uterus (mammals) or to the outside (fish, birds).
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the physical magnitude of the tube through which the ova pass from the ovary to the uterus (mammals) or to the outside (fish, birds).
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the morphology or physiology of the female reproductive gland containing the germ cells during its formation and differentiation.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the physical magnitude of the tube that conducts the urine from the renal pelvis to the bladder.
The distance from side to side of the tube that conducts the urine from the renal pelvis to the bladder.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the function of or processes in the tube that conducts the urine from the renal pelvis to the urinary bladder.
The distance from side to side of the canal that leads from the bladder and discharges urine externally.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the physical magnitude of the canal that leads from the bladder and discharges urine externally.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the physical magnitude of the organ of copulation and urination in the male.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the function of or processes in the filtering unit of the kidney that includes the renal corpuscle, proximal and distal convoluted tubules, loop of Henle, and the collecting tubule.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the function of or processes in the gland surrounding the beginning of the urethra in males that secretes part of the seminal fluid.
The proportion or number of cells in the external sac of skin that encloses the testes.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the morphology or physiology of the inner portion of the kidney during its formation and differentiation.
